m;">Loot Policy for Tavern Heroes</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:small;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>General Raids</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--> (more than two full groups):</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
<!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:small;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Epic Raids</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--> (Mob requires at least 1 full group):</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Official Rules</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;font-size:small;">1. Starting Points</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
All Guild members will start with 0 points.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;font-size:small;">2. Event Points</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
Each event will yield 1 point to each person who is present for the major duration of the event.  Events will need to be oked by a guild officer. (Please read the note at the bottom on epic mobs, they are given 1 pt for the event but the mob must require at least 1 full group.)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;font-size:small;">3. When Points are awarded</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
Points will be awarded at the end of an event, what determins an event is decided by the point manager and/or guild leader. Events are based on many factors, including time, type of mobs and zone.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;font-size:small;">4. /guildremove</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
Removing yourself from the guild and choosing/being allowed to return will result in forfeiture of all existing points and having to start fresh as a new member.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;font-size:small;">5. Knowning your point total.</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
Every member is required to know his/her latest point total from the guild board. Board values always are used for rolls.<br>
If you do not agree with your point total, you must dispute the point total before the raid.  POINTS WILL NOT BE CHANGED DURING A RAID.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;font-size:small;">6. Upgrade Value:</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
All items have a point value that is required to be in the Lotto for this item. There are two categories of items. Minor upgrades and Major upgrades.<br>
<br>
Minor upgrades will have a value between 0 and 10pts.<br>
Major upgrades will have a value between 15 and 35pts<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;font-size:small;">7. Who can lotto?</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
Lotto is allowed if you possess the FULL value of a given item for the character present at the event and if the character bidding can use the desired item. If no participant possess the full value for this item, a roll will still happen but the person who wins will have their points set back to zero.<br>
<br>
Droppable items are allocated only if a participant posses the full value for the item or if that participant is willing to go to a negative value in points.<br>
<br>
Also note, that members on probation (2 weeks) are not allowed to participate on lottoes.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;font-size:small;">8. Guests and Alts.</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
Guests looting is limited to items that cannot be carried over by a member, as well as alt loot.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;font-size:small;">9. Looting on the same target?</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
Lottoes are exclusive. In the case of Multiple item drops from a creature, participation to lotto is limited only to ONE of the dropped items (participation for spells and free items are not included in this).<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:maroon;font-size:small;">10. How we deal with our point system.</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
Lotto on item is done using the current lotto rules.<br>
<br>
- At the beginning of each raid we will set a max lotto number. We do this by taking the person with the most points in the raid, taking that number times 10 and adding 100 points.  This will give us our max lotto number.<br>
<br>
- Every person then rolls from their point total times 10 to the max lotto number, and highest wins the item.<br>
<br>
Here is an example:<br>
<br>
Fonker shows up to the raid with 8 points.<br>
Aerynne shows up to the raid with 3 points.<br>
Emmers shows up to the raid with 2 points.<br>
<br>
From the system above, we would see that Fonker has the most points.  We take his total 8*10 which gives us 80, then we add 100.  Max lotto number is 180.<br>
Everyone on the raid will be rolling the high number as 180.<br>
<br>
Then you take Fonkers original number 80 and have him roll.. /random 80 180<br>
<br>
Fonker = /random 80 180<br>
Aerynne = /random 30 180<br>
Emmers = /random 20 180<br>
<br>
Our largest max number will be 1100.  Which means even if Fonker has 120 points, we use only 100 points for the roll itself.<br>
<br>
Example:<br>
<br>
Fonker 300 points.<br>
Aerynne 150 points.<br>
Emmers 80 points.<br>
<br>
Our max number is 1100, since we have someone over the point value of 100.  If your over 100 points, we figure your lotto start number from 100.<br>
<br>
Fonkers original number would then be 100, so he would roll.. /random 1000 1100<br>
<br>
Fonker = /random 1000 1100<br>
Aerynne = /random 1000 1100<br>
Emmers = /random 800 1100<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;font-size:small;">11. Item cost.</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
Minor upgrades diminish your point bank by their value. There will be a &quot;winners&quot; list for minor upgrades kept for the last week. ( so you cannot win 2 minor upgrades per week unless no one needs ).<br>
<br>
Major upgrades cost you half your total points.  (So if fonker has 300 points, the item would cost him 150 points total.)<br>
<br>
In the case of someone who does not have enough points for an item. That person's point total is reduced to 0. There is an exception in the case of a droppable item. Droppable items are kept in guild bank until the winner has enough points or accept to go to a negative value of points at the moment of the win.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;font-size:small;">12. How points are calculated.</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
· Points are gained after an event.<br>
· Points are updated manually by a human person that updates them as often and as fast as possible. Thus the board status at any given date is a snap shot of the last update done. It is not necessarily your real value, but that’s a fair value for everyone since everyone is in the same possible snapshot status.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>NOTE:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Epic loot will be given to the person who setup the raid for that part of the epic.  Each person who attended the epic raid except for the person who got the epic pieace gets 1 point.  The mob must require 1 full group to complete the epic pieace, and the points have to be awarded by an officer/guild leader to that group.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>NOTE:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Major Upgrades will be declared by the Raid Commander.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>NOTE:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Once a player has won loot, he/she can not win more loot from that target. (there are always exceptions to this rule, cash items and droppable items may fall into this category)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>NOTE:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Any quest item to drop on a raid, should go to the person closest to the end of the quest.  This is a NBG rule.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>NOTE:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Most cash items that can not be useable to guild members such as junk, will be sold and that cash will be donated to the guild bank.<br>
